<title>Callums Chilli</title>
<filename>callums_chilli.xml</filename>
<thumbnail>callums_chilli.jpeg</thumbnail>
<category>Dinner</category>
<category>Lunch</category>
<diet>Vegan</diet>
<diet>GFO</diet>
<diet>LowSugar</diet>
<diet>Keto</diet>
<yield>6</yield>
<prepTime>PT20M</prepTime>
<cookTime>PT20M</cookTime>
<ingredient>3 cans chopped tomatoes </ingredient>
<ingredient>2 cans kidney beans</ingredient>
<ingredient>2 cans black beans</ingredient>
<ingredient>1 can corn</ingredient>
<ingredient>3 sweet potatoes peeled and chopped </ingredient>
<ingredient>2-3 TBsp olive oil</ingredient>
<ingredient>2-4 garlic cloves crushed </ingredient>
<ingredient>2 teaspoon cumin </ingredient>
<ingredient>1/2 teaspoon coriander and chilli </ingredient>
<ingredient>salt and pepper to taste</ingredient>
<ingredient>Colourful peppers for garnish (if desired)</ingredient>
<step>Heat oil in large pot and cook garlic for a few minutes.</step>
<step>Add spices and cook for another minute or two.</step>
<step>Add sweet potatoes and stir to coat.</step>
<step>Add chopped tomatoes and cook until sweet potatoes cooked, but not mushy (about 10-20 minutes.)</step>
<step>Rinse and drain all cans and add to pot.</step>
<step>Add salt and pepper if using.</step>
<step>Taste and add additional spices if necessary.</step>
<step>Serve with any or all of grated cheese, guacamole, salsa, sour cream, chopped peppers, grated carrots, shredded lettuce, corn chips and flat bread.</step>
</recipe>

